 driving laws and policies biased against those different from us. Overcoming intolerance requires consistent application of universal principles of respect for conscience. Just as important, it requires greater understanding. Nussbaum challenges us to embrace freedom of religious observance for all, extending to others what we demand for ourselves. She encourages us to expand our capacity for empathetic imagination by cultivating our curiosity, seeking friendship across religious lines, and establishing a consistent ethic of decency and civility. With this greater understanding and respect, Nussbaum argues, we can rise above the politics of fear and toward a more open and inclusive future.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 08. Jul 2019) 70(DE-601)1042796050(DE-588)4121582-5aReligiöse Toleranz2gnd 70(DE-601)10546452X0(DE-588)4162166-9aIntoleranz2gnd 70(DE-601)1057420900(DE-588)4125186-6aReligionsfreiheit2gnd 70(DE-601)1063946300(DE-588)4002053-8aAngst2gnd 7aRELIGION / Religious Intolerance, Persecution & Conflict.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertHUP Complete eBook Package 2011-2014z978311037488908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertHUP eBook Package 2012z978311037491908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertHUP eBook Package Backlist 2000-2013z978311044220508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertHUP eBook Package Backlist 2000-2014z978311045951708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertHUP eBook Package Backlist 2000-2015z978311066256640uhttps://doi.org/10.4159/harvard.9780674065918423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780674065918.jpg  a978-3-11-037488-9  HUP Complete eBook Package 2011-2014  a978-3-11-037491-9  HUP eBook Package 2012b2012  a978-3-11-044220-5  HUP eBook Package Backlist 2005-2013c2000d2013  a978-3-11-0459